td.content: Patient is a pleasant 60-year-old female here for evaluation of right-sided neck pain, right shoulder and arm pain. She reports associated numbness and tingling in the right upper extremity. She states this is ongoing for about 2 months without injury. On exam she has pain with range of motion of the right shoulder and she also has a positive Spurling's, signs and symptoms consistent with cervical radiculopathy. she has significant degenerative changes in the lower cervical spine and arthritis in the right shoulder based on x-rays. based on her history, physical exam, as well as x-ray findings I feel that her symptoms are related to cervical radiculopathy as well as arthritis in the right shoulder. We discussed options today. Recommend starting conservatively with medication management. We will start her on a Medrol Dosepak, and then meloxicam afterwards. She requested pain medication. I will call in a short course to take needed and we discussed side effects, potential for addiction and abuse. Educated patient on safe opioid use and offered prescription for Narcan/naloxone due to medication prescribed today. Patient declined prescription. Discussed that if she continues to have pain in her shoulder especially pain with range of motion and movement, recommend she comes back for a right shoulder injection. Given her history of diabetes do not recommend doing steroid injection as well as Medrol Dosepak and given her radicular symptoms I feel starting with MDP is more appropriate. We reviewed and discussed steroid use today including risk of GI Upset, hyperglycemia, agitation, and long term risks. Patient verbalized understanding and agreement. I reviewed with the patient regarding NSAID use, potential side effects, and precautions. I have reviewed the patient's medication list in light of potential NSAID use. Cervical exercises given. will plan for follow-up in the spine clinic in 4-6 weeks, and again discussed that if her right shoulder pain persist as specially pain with range of motion she may return for potential steroid injection into the shoulder. She verbalized understanding. Answered questions to the best of my ability. The plan is agreed with and understood.
